cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.HC 

This paper focuses on the interaction between human mobility and social relations, which falls under the scope of social networks and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a mixture model and exploits check-in data, which involves database and information retrieval techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper investigates the practical applications of location sociality, which involves human-computer interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a possible sub-category.
